<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{x}-{6}{y}={15}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{6}{x}-{3}{y}={66}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({9},-{4}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}+-{6}{y}={15}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}={15}-{\left(-{6}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{{15}-{\left(-{6}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{1}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{\left(\frac{{{15}-{\left(-{6}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{1}}}}\right)}+-{3}{y}={66}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{6}}{{-{{1}}}}\cdot{\left({15}\right)}-\frac{{6}}{{-{{1}}}}{\left(-{6}\right)}{y}+-{3}{y}={66}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{90}-{\left(-{36}\right)}{y}+-{3}{y}={66}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{36}{y}+{\left(-{3}\right)}{y}={66}--{90}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{36}{y}+{\left(-{3}\right)}{y}={156}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{36}+{\left(-{3}\right)}\right)}{y}={156}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{39}{y}={156}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{156}}{{-{{39}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-{4}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}+-{6}{\left(-{4}\right)}={15}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}+{\left({24}\right)}={15}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}={15}-{\left({24}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{1}{x}=-{9}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{9}}{{-{{1}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={9}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({9},-{4}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

